# QA Estimation Calculator — Project Overview

Internal tool for A Positive Future. Lets a test engineer calibrate an estimation
model and an account manager run a client intake to generate a QA schedule.

## Stack
- React 18 + TypeScript (strict) + Vite + Tailwind CSS
- Built with vite-plugin-singlefile → one self-contained index.html
- HashRouter (not BrowserRouter) so file:// URLs work from a Teams folder
- No backend. No database. No authentication.
- State: React Context + useReducer (AppContext)
- Persistence: localStorage (session) + JSON file import/export

## Two roles, three views
- Engineer → /calibrate (7-step wizard, exports testing-model.json)
- Account manager → /intake (10-section form) → /schedule (pivot matrix + export)

## File sharing model
The engineer exports testing-model.json. It lives in a shared Teams folder.
Account managers import it at the start of each project intake session.
Projects are saved as project-*.json and can be reloaded the same way.
